The paper discusses the development of principles for software citation and the challenges that remain in implementing them. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories, including digital libraries (cs.DL), software engineering (cs.SE), cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and information retrieval (cs.IR). However, given the focus on citation and publication, cs.DL and cs.SE are the most likely sub-categories.
